{"id": 227498198, "title": "Japan, South Korea and U.S. unveil new initiatives to cement defense ties", "text": "Singapore - The defense chiefs of Japan, the United States and South Korea used a meeting at Asia\u2019s top regional security conference Sunday to announce a series of new initiatives that will help formalize their burgeoning trilateral defense cooperation.At a gathering on the sidelines of the Shangri-La Dialogue in Singapore, Defense Minister Minoru Kihara, U.S. Defense Secretary Lloyd Austin and South Korean defense chief Shin Won-sik agreed to develop a framework to institutionalize trilateral cooperation within the year.The push comes as fears grow over possible lapses in U.S. commitment to the region should former U.S. President Donald Trump be re-elected in November. It also comes amid concerns that political changes in Seoul in Tokyo could scuttle the hard-fought cooperative agreements already reached.", "summary": "The three partner nations agreed to develop a framework to institutionalize trilateral cooperation within the year.", "url": "https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2024/06/02/japan/politics/south-korea-japan-us-trilateral-shangri-la/", "image": "https://www.japantimes.co.jp/japantimes/uploads/images/2024/06/02/400727.JPG", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-02 12:09:00", "author": "Gabriel Dominguez,Web Master", "authors": ["Gabriel Dominguez", "Web Master"], "language": "en", "source_country": "JP", "sentiment": -0.119}